body: @adriacabeza Hi, where did you obtain the binary? If you built it yourself, have you enabled TENSORRT support?
the failure is "Network must have at least one output" when building TRT network (graph). @adriacabeza is it possible to share the converted model to repro the issue?

This is where failure happened,
[2019-05-23 15:29:51   ERROR] Parameter check failed at: ../builder/Network.cpp::addInput::432, condition: isValidDims(dims)

Are there dynamic shapes on the inputs?
if there's dynamic shape inputs, then TRT should not return the sub-graph in GetCapability, right? @stevenlix

TRT parser won't check dynamic shape until this PR (https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/1012) checked in. Please try the latest master code, or if possible share the model so that I can take a look.

I've tried the latest master version of the repo and it seems that the issue about the variable dimensions is solved, but now I get a segmentation fault (core dumped) when rt.InferenceSession(my_onnx_model):

```python

 ```
About the binary model, I cannot attach the model since it is too big to insert it here. That is why I was asking for your email.

Email systems have their limits as well.

I tried tar, tar.gz, zip and 7z and the compression rate was really low for all of them.

 However, not long ago I was told I cannot share the model for external issues, so I am trying to replicate it by myself with another dataset.

@adriacabeza do you still need assistance to debug this? If you cannot share the entire model, sharing part of it that causes the issue can also help. If it's no longer an issue, please close this, thanks!
